This article is a transcript of remarks given by Vice President Mike Pence and his wife Karen Pence at an event celebrating military families at the White House. Mrs. Pence introduces Marlon Bundo, the family bunny, who has his own Instagram account and is the "Bunny of the United States" (BOTUS). The Vice President expresses gratitude to military families for their sacrifices and announces that May is National Military Appreciation Month. He also recognizes military spouses and those named Military Spouse of the Year. The Vice President promises that the Trump administration is committed to supporting and rebuilding the military. The event concludes with thanks and applause for the military families in attendance.